/* this file contain the cumulative distribution for the exit point for the SRW on Z^2 starting from the origin stopped
   when it touches a point in the inner boundary of the box [-R,R]^2. 

   Call (x,y) this point. Then either (|x] = R and |y|<R) or (|y| = R and |x| < R). Call z the abosolute value of the
   coordinate which is not equal to +/-R. Therefore 0 <= z < R. The array below give the CDF for the point Z ie

   SRWexitGrid_R_CDF[i] = P[ Z <= i] for i \in 0,1,...,R.

   All values in the array are exact up to double precision. 

   The arrays were obtained by computing the solution for the corresponding harmonic problem using a multigrid method
   for solving the Poisson equation with Dirichlet condition: see program 'SRWExitGridProblem' used for creating them.
*/


